.TH "ssam_request_sync_init" 9 "ssam_request_sync_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_request_sync_init \- Initialize a synchronous request struct.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssam_request_sync_init
.BI "(struct ssam_request_sync *rqst "  ","
.BI "enum ssam_request_flags flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rqst" 12
The request to initialize.
.IP "flags" 12
The request flags.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initializes the given request struct. Does not initialize the request
message data. This has to be done explicitly after this call via
\fBssam_request_sync_set_data\fP and the actual message data has to be written
via \fBssam_request_write_data\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns zero on success or -EINVAL if the given flags are invalid.
